The paper deals with facial image analysis, specifically 3-D face alignment and UV maps. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of attributes such as age and identity, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the challenges of dealing with missing information and outliers, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
